        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 3:51PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 350 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pleasant Grove, or 12 miles southwest of Senatobia, moving northeast
at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Barr, Wakefield, Cockrum, Aiken, Crossroad, Tyro, Senatobia, Como,
Chulahoma, Glenville, Pleasant Grove, Coldwater, Poagville, Horatio,
Cypress Corner, Bluff, Looxahoma, Sardis, Lurline, and Alphaba.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for northwestern
Mississippi.</instruction>
